<section
  class='fullscreen-section'
  id='about'
  data-title='About — Katja Turnsek | Front-End Developer & Designer'
  data-description='Front-end developer and designer with a background in visual design, building responsive, accessible websites with JavaScript, React, REST APIs, CSS, and thoughtful UI.'
>
  <div class='rows'>
    <div class='row'>
      <h1>About</h1>
      <h2>Front-End Developer with a Designer’s Eye</h2>
      <p class='align-right-60'>
        I'm a
        <strong>front-end developer and designer</strong>
        with a background in visual design, branding, illustration, and digital interfaces. I build
        responsive websites that combine
        <strong>clear structure</strong>,
        <strong>accessible UI</strong>, and
        <strong>careful visual detail</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class='row'>
      <h3>My Story</h3>
      <p>
        My background started in visual design, where I worked with branding, illustration, web
        design, touchscreen interfaces, and digital layouts. That experience still shapes how I
        approach front-end work: I pay close attention to hierarchy, spacing, rhythm, colour, and
        how an interface feels in use.
      </p>
      <p>
        After completing front-end development studies at Noroff, I have focused on building
        portfolio projects with
        <strong>semantic HTML</strong>,
        <strong>modern CSS</strong>,
        <strong>JavaScript</strong>,
        <strong>React</strong>, and
        <strong>REST API integration</strong>. My recent work includes e-commerce, auction, booking,
        and portfolio websites with responsive layouts, reusable UI patterns, authentication, and
        API-driven content.
      </p>
      <p>
        I like building interfaces that feel calm, structured, and easy to understand, but still
        have a clear visual identity. Outside of code, I paint
        <strong>fine-art pet portraits</strong>
        in oils and create logos, graphics, and UI details. Whether I work with pixels, code, or
        paint, the goal is the same:
        <strong>clarity</strong>,
        <strong>quality</strong>, and
        <strong>human connection</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class='row'>
      <h3>Skills at a Glance</h3>
    </div>

    <div class='animated-bars'>
      <div class='bar-stack'>
        <div class='bar bar-bg'></div>
        <div class='bar bar-1'><span class='bar-label'>DESIGN &amp; PROTOTYPING</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class='bar-stack'>
        <div class='bar bar-bg'></div>
        <div class='bar bar-2'><span class='bar-label'>WEB DEVELOPMENT</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class='bar-stack'>
        <div class='bar bar-bg'></div>
        <div class='bar bar-3'><span class='bar-label'>GRAPHIC DESIGN</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='row'>
      <div class='demo-links'>
        <a
          href='{{base}}assets/pdf/Katja_Turnsek_FrontEnd_Designer_CV.pdf'
          target='_blank'
          class='label-link online-demo-label'
          rel='noopener'
        >
          <span class='label-text'>Download CV (PDF)</span>
          <svg class='icon icon-18 arrow-icon' aria-hidden='true'><use
              href='#i-arrow-right'
            /></svg>
        </a>
        <a
          href='https://github.com/KatjaTurnsek'
          target='_blank'
          class='label-link online-demo-label'
          rel='noopener'
        >
          <span class='label-text'>View GitHub</span>
          <svg class='icon icon-18 arrow-icon' aria-hidden='true'><use
              href='#i-arrow-right'
            /></svg>
        </a>
        <a
          href='{{base}}#contact'
          class='label-link online-demo-label'
          aria-label='Go to contact section'
        >
          <span class='label-text'>Contact Me</span>
          <svg class='icon icon-18 arrow-icon' aria-hidden='true'><use
              href='#i-arrow-right'
            /></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class='testimonial-section'>
    <div class='testimonial'>
      <div class='testimonial-label'>
        <svg class='icon icon-14 arrow-icon' aria-hidden='true'><use href='#i-arrow-down' /></svg>
        <h3 class='label-text'>Testimonials</h3>
      </div>
      <div class='circle-button'>
        <svg class='icon' aria-hidden='true'><use href='#i-comment' /></svg>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class='rows'>
    <div class='row'>
      <figure class='testimonial-card'>
        <blockquote>
          “Katja is creative by nature and approaches every assignment with great dedication. Her
          work combines strong visual sense with clear structure, and she takes pride in delivering
          well-crafted, functional designs. Always positive, outgoing, and easy to collaborate with,
          a true professional and a pleasure to have on the team.”
        </blockquote>
        <figcaption>
          <span class='author'>Damjan Strucl</span>
          <span class='role'>CEO, Logina d.o.o</span>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <div class='row'>
      <figure class='testimonial-card'>
        <blockquote>
          “We are extremely happy with the logo and CD cover design created by Katja Turnsek. Her
          work perfectly captured the spirit and identity of Heart Asylum, combining creativity and
          professionalism throughout the process. We highly recommend her for any visual design
          projects.”
        </blockquote>
        <figcaption>
          <span class='author'>Heart Asylum</span>
          <span class='role'>Alternative Rock Duo</span>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <div class='back-to-work-container'>
      <a
        href='{{base}}'
        class='label-link back-to-work-label'
        data-back
        data-back-fallback='{{base}}'
        aria-label='Go back'
      >
        <svg class='icon icon-18 arrow-icon' aria-hidden='true'><use href='#i-arrow-left' /></svg>
        <span class='label-text'>Back to Home</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>